bowed not: Yichra welo yishtachaweh, "bowed not down, nor prostrated
himself," or worshipped him. Had this meant only civil reverence the
king would not have needed to command it; nor would Mordecai have
refused it; there was, therefore, some kind of divine honour intended,
such as was paid to the Persian kings, and which even the Greeks
refused, as express adoration. [Est
